<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,510,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,541,546,572]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species (reported as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lohmann" authorityYear="1889" box="[845,1063,546,572]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Halacarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="murrayi">
<emphasis box="[845,1063,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Halacarus murrayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was found among sponges and algae (Lohmann 1889). This species was also reported in empty 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[944,1019,583,609]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Ostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[944,1019,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Ostrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
valves extensively pitted by sponge 
<taxonomicName box="[198,313,618,645]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Cliona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clionaida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[198,274,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Cliona</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from New Haven harbour, Long Island Sound, Eastern North America (Newell 1947).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,510,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,654,680]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Remarks:</emphasis>
This was recorded on various substrata: sediments, algae, sponges, and bryozoans from Boreal North Atlantic, European and American shores (Newell 1947; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I." box="[826,984,690,716]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="143 - 178" refId="ref13534" refString="Bartsch, I. (1998 a) Halacarinae (Acari, Halacaroidea) from the northwestern Black Sea: A review. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 95, 143 - 178." type="journal article" year="1998">Bartsch1998a</bibRefCitation>
; Chatterjee 2022). This species was also found amongst cuticular structures of spider crab 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[771,989,726,752]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Libinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emarginata">
<emphasis box="[771,989,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Libinia emarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Arthropoda, Crustacea, 
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1432,726,752]" class="Malacostraca" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="class">Malacostraca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[198,312,762,789]" class="Malacostraca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Decapoda</taxonomicName>
) from 
<collectingRegion box="[388,539,762,788]" country="United States of America" name="Rhode Island" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Rhode Island</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[550,604,762,788]" name="United States of America" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I." box="[619,772,762,788]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 62" refId="ref12865" refString="Bartsch, I. (1979) Halacaridae (Acari) von der Atlantikkuste Nordamerikas. Beschreibung der Arten. Mikrofauna des Meeresbodens, 79, 1 - 62." type="journal article" year="1979">Bartsch 1979</bibRefCitation>
a; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chatterjee, T." box="[797,992,762,788]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="155 - 166" refId="ref14730" refString="Chatterjee, T. (2021 a) A checklist of halacarid mites (Acari: Halacaridae) associated with decapod crustaceans (Arthropoda, Crustacea, Decapoda). Persian Journal of Acarology, 10 (2), 155 - 166. https: // doi. org / 10.22073 / pja. v 10 i 2.65624" type="journal article" year="2021">Chatterjee 2021a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
